			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Lithium Carbonate Production ; Battery Grade Lithium Carbonate ; Sulfuric Acid ; Australia Exports Lithium Spodumene Concentrate</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">碳酸锂生产 ; 电池级碳酸锂 ; 硫酸法 ; 澳大利亚出口锂辉石精矿</baseName>
			</name>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification>
					<common:class level="0">Unit processes</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="2">Inorganic chemicals</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Once spodumene has been concentrated, lithium compounds(LiOH•H2O or Li2CO3) can be produced from it. A cathode plant environmental impact assessment report produced by the Tianqi Lithium Corporation, a major cathode producer in China, details the inputs of material, energy, and water it uses to produce 1 tonne of LiOH•H2O or Li2CO3. Their report assumes concentrated spodumene ore from western Australia at 6% concentration. Since we assumed the concentrated spodumene ore has a minimum of 5% concentration, it issufficient for the production process here. We assume that the spodumene is shipped from coastal western Australia to China and transported 100 miles (161 km) by truck (33 tonne payload) to a lithium compounds facility. Note that these shipping estimations are not specific to thereporting company but to concentrated production regions in China.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">将锂辉石精炼浓缩后，就可以生产出锂化合物（氢氧化锂或碳酸锂）。中国主要的正极生产商天齐锂业公司的一份正极厂环境影响评估报告详细说明了生产 1 吨 LiOH-H2O 或 Li2CO3 所需的材料、能源和水的投入。 他们的报告假设澳大利亚西部的精矿为浓度为 6% 的锂辉石。由于我们假定精矿的浓度至少为 5%，因此足以满足此处生产工艺的需要。我们假定，锂辉石从澳大利亚西部沿海运到中国，再用卡车（载重 33 吨）运输 100 英里（161 公里）到锂化合物工厂。请注意，这些运输估算并非针对报告公司，而是针对中国的集中生产地区。</common:generalComment>
		</dataSetInformation>
